ce:section.ce:para:
The UV–vis absorption spectrum is the first applied method to characterize the phthalocyanines. Pcs are known with the characteristic absorption in their electronic spectra. One is the Q band arising in the visible area at between 600–700 nm and the other one is B band came out in the UV region between 300–350 nm [42]. The absorption spectra of the prepared ZnPcs (3) were examined in 1 × 10−5 M concentration of DMSO solution. Q band absorption of Pcs (3,4) were observed at 687 and 685 nm, respectively (Table 1
                        ) and the other characteristic band (B bands) were observed at 336 and 357 nm, respectively. (Fig. 2
                        ).
